ated list, +of roles to a user., +, +//`-h, --help`:: Returns all of the command parameters., +, +`list`:: List the users that are registered with the `file` realm, +on the local node. If you also specify a user name, the command provides, +information for that user., +, +`-p <password>`:: Specifies the user's password. If you do not specify this, +parameter, the command prompts you for the password., ++, +--, +TIP: Omit the `-p` option to keep, +plaintext passwords out of the terminal session's command history., +, +--, +, +`passwd <username>`:: Resets a user's password. You can specify the new, +password directly with the `-p` parameter., +, +`-r <roles>`::, +* If used with the `useradd` parameter, defines a user's roles. This option]